The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Suicide by ex-envoy

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Sept. 6: Former Indian ambassador to Denmark and Tunisia, Ramesh Chand Shukla, was found dead in a garbage chute of the posh IFS Apartments in Mayur Vihar in east Delhi today.

 Police said 64-year-old Shukla had died after he jumped off the building. The police found a suicide note that Shukla had written to his wife.

 Shukla, who had retired from the Indian Foreign Service three years ago, is survived by his wife and two daughters. He and his wife lived in the apartments, while their daughters were residing in the US. The police said Shuklas wife had filed an FIR when she found her husband missing on returning from a shopping trip on Sunday evening. 




